{
  "texts": [
    "We define elastic energy of a vertex at coordinate p as the sum of elastic energies connected to that vertex.",
    "The elastic energy map Ω for a field F is a mapping between pixel coordinates and the elastic energy of the vertex associated with that coordinate,",
    "We define elastic regularizer L er as the masked average of elastic energies for tissue vertices in the source image, L er = ψðΩðFÞ,TðM s FÞÞ: ð8Þ",
    "For a given resolution, the inputs to an image pair aligner are a source and target image, M s, M t, and the output is a displacement field F and image encodings Q s and Q t.",
    "The aligner is trained in two stages with two loss functions."
  ]
}